cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.EM 

The paper deals with using deep learning techniques to extract meaningful results from images of plasmonic structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the study of electromagnetic properties of plasmonic structures, which falls under the sub-category cs.EM (Electromagnetism).
